apl_event.field_event_summary: Designed for young learners, Imagination Station encourages learning through play. Explore the arts, practice your motor skills, and start your STEM exploration.

apl_event.title: Kids Create
apl_event.field_event_summary: Kids Create focuses on literary inspiration! Enjoy a story and create a work of art based on the book. This month we're exploring the paintings of Jean-Michel Basquiat. Recommended for ages 5 and up.

apl_event.field_event_summary: Bring your teddy bears and a picnic blanket to join us for a special bear-themed event with songs, stories, and big body play. In case of rain, program will be held in the meeting room.

apl_event.title: Teddy Bear Picnic
apl_event.field_event_summary: Bring your teddy bear or other stuffed friend! This storytime celebration is full of bear-themed stories, songs, and crafts or activities.

apl_event.body: Join us as we begin a tour in the Gallery on the second floor and work our way up to each of the 3rd, 4th, 5th and 6th floors to view and learn about the art exhibited - permanent and rotating - at the Central Library.

apl_event.title: Science Friday
apl_event.field_event_summary: Come for an hour of seasonally-themed STEAM stations or science design challenges the whole family will enjoy. Create, build, solve, and learn more about the natural world around us. This hands-on science workshop is designed for children ages 5 and up.

SCORE Workshop - Taxes for Small Business
apl_event.field_event_summary: Lisa Bargsley will identify the types of tax forms for different business entities, when taxes are due, and how taxes are calculated.

apl_event.title: SCORE Workshop - Lending for New Small Businesses
apl_event.field_event_summary: Learn how to manage cash flow and credit for your business. Ryan defines three types of cash flow and discusses solutions and potential loans to meet your credit needs.

apl_event.title: Literature Live! Presents Wiley and the Hairy Man
Emailing 101 Workshop
apl_event.body:
This workshop is in English and Spanish | Este taller es en inglés y español.

Austin Free-Net, in partnership with the Austin Public Library (Terrazas Branch), presents: Emailing 101 Workshop; Instructor: Jasmin Vargas. To be successful in this workshop, you will need: a device (smart phone or tablet), internet access, and an email account. This workshop is an introduction to emailing with useful tips and tricks to stay organized and connected through email.

Como usar tu correo electrónico; Instructora: Jasmin Vargas. Para tener éxito en esta clase, necesitarás: un dispositivo (computadora, laptop, teléfono inteligente, tableta), acceso a Internet y una cuenta de correo electrónico.  Este taller cubrirá una breve introducción al correo electrónico y cómo sacar el máximo provecho de las muchas funciones del correo electrónico.

Registration for workshops is not required. For questions, please contact Austin Free-Net at access@austinfree.net or (512) 236-8225. 

No es necesario registrarse para los Talleres. Si tiene preguntas, comuníquese con Austin Free-Net en access@austinfree.net o (512) 236-8225.

apl_event.title: Family Archiving 101
apl_event.field_event_summary: In this workshop, participants will learn the basics of Family Archiving. Archivists will teach the basics of preservation, share examples of poorly preserved materials, and demonstrate preservation techniques.
